# LLM-assisted development (essentials)

**Read order:** [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) → this file (always on) → **changing-pulp-upload** + [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) for `upload`/Tekton consumers → **changing-pulp-container** for `Dockerfile`/`.tekton/` image build → [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) when touching multiple packages. **On-demand skills:** [.cursor/rules/llm-development-guidelines-deep.mdc](llm-development-guidelines-deep.mdc) (skill index).

## Domain

- **Pulp** API semantics: [pulpproject.org](https://pulpproject.org/)
- **Commands & conventions:** `AGENTS.md` · **Konflux contracts:** `CLAUDE.md` · **Code map:** `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Pull requests and CHANGELOG

- **Do not** paste a full PR body every turn. If the turn might become a PR, **ask once** if the user wants paste-ready PR text.
- **After they confirm:** load **drafting-pulp-tool-pr** skill — PR text follows `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md` verbatim; include suggested commit (`Assisted-By:` + `Signed-off-by:` per `.github/commit-message-template.txt`) and **`CHANGELOG.md`** under `[Unreleased]` when notable — **same turn**.
- **No** `CHANGELOG` edits on every debug fix unless the user asks.
- **Merge gate:** **100% diff coverage** on the PR diff (`make test-diff-coverage`). If it fails, use **fixing-diff-cover-failures** skill.

## After code changes (mandatory)

1. `make lint` → fix issues
2. `make format`
3. `pre-commit run --all-files` → **loop** until **zero** failures
4. `make test` (full suite) → **loop** until green
5. `git fetch origin` → `make test-diff-coverage` (use `COMPARE_BRANCH=origin/<base>` if not targeting `main`) → **loop** until diff is fully covered

Do not treat the branch as PR-ready without clean pre-commit, green tests, and passing diff-cover.

